doc.after: Birmingham is chiefly a product of the 18th 19th and 20th centuries its growth began during the Industrial Revolution Consequently relatively few buildings survive from its earlier history and those that do are protected There are 1 946 listed buildings in Birmingham and thirteen scheduled ancient monuments 201 Birmingham City Council also operate a locally listing scheme for buildings that do not fully meet the criteria for statutorily listed status
